Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.48,0:04:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.52,0:04:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It knows where it is locally, but it doesn't really have any point of self-correction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.08,0:04:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So if the instruments on the ship are off, the ship will be lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.40,0:04:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And over time, they have, of course, at the bottom of the Great Lakes are the wrecks of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.18,0:04:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,6,000 ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.18,0:04:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Just at the bottom of the Great Lakes, that's rather amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.56,0:05:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So not having a compass to tell you truth from falsehood is why mankind barely survives.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.63,0:05:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So the map of consciousness, then, is picking up on essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.66,0:05:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the main themes of these lectures is to differentiate appearance, what a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.46,0:05:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,looks like, or what you think about it, or what's your opinion in, from essence, which
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.96,0:05:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is independent of what you think about it, or how it's pictured, or how it's projected
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.70,0:05:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.70,0:05:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality, then, is self-confirmatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.35,0:05:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So on a scale of 1 to 1,000, you can calibrate the relative energy of the essence of anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.16,0:05:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.26,0:05:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about consciousness, which is more comprehensible from quantum mechanics, is non-locality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.44,0:06:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The essence of consciousness, it has no beginning, it has no end, it has no midpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.46,0:06:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.49,0:06:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no here, and it has no there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.49,0:06:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no now, and it has no then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.49,0:06:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what the heck all that means, but it sure sounds impressive, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.46,0:06:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In essence, it means we can calibrate the level of consciousness of Cleopatra, as well
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.92,0:06:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as Mrs. Clinton, or what's that crazy lady on TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.02,0:06:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,She rants and raves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.26,0:06:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.90,0:06:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Rosie.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.90,0:06:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Rosie, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.70,0:06:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All her favorite people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.62,0:06:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I love Rosie, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.48,0:06:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can make millions being mad as a hatter, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.48,0:06:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.48,0:06:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to be sane, logical, anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.88,0:06:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.88,0:06:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.88,0:06:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's America.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.04,0:07:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.04,0:07:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can calibrate, then, by consciousness picks up the essence of things, and the reason
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.36,0:07:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it does so, because the evolution of life in this planet, as we've said before, the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.86,0:07:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,most primitive protozoa has no energy within itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.49,0:07:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like chlorophyll green plants just sit there and enjoy the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.43,0:07:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is protoplasmic has to obtain energy from out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.83,0:07:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, it has to be able to diagnose what's edible and what's lethal, what will
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.33,0:07:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,kill you and what will support life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.28,0:07:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's an intuitive knowingness, you know, that it derives as an essence of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.58,0:07:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.58,0:07:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.58,0:07:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.58,0:07:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the secret of life itself, especially in its expression as protoplasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.89,0:08:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,On this scale of consciousness, the way it turned out, the scale is arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.22,0:08:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We could have picked one to a million or any other number, but as long as it's the same
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.36,0:08:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,point of reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.86,0:08:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's pretty much like a thermometer or an altimeter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.40,0:08:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have no personal feelings about calibrated numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.18,0:08:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Other times I hear critics, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.06,0:08:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he said this, or he said that, I didn't say anything, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.00,0:08:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't say anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.84,0:08:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't even care about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.40,0:08:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do I care what the pyramids in Egypt calibrate at?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.96,0:08:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.80,0:08:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't own them or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.85,0:08:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't have any vested interest
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.29,0:08:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in what things calibrate at.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.05,0:08:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Having done tens of thousands of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.45,0:08:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we've gotten to be able to pretty much guess in advance
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.57,0:08:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,at least what range a thing is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.33,0:08:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But occasionally, we're surprised, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.77,0:09:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The presumption is that it would come out in a certain value,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.61,0:09:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and it comes out quite differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.65,0:09:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, then we look elsewhere to see
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.55,0:09:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the explanation of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.06,0:09:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, the one that upset some people
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.13,0:09:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,was we said that earth warming is not due to human at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.91,0:09:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the angry blogs and everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.01,0:09:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You see people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.41,0:09:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,F you, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.59,0:09:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.17,0:09:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I get such nice emails sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.52,0:09:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we got, no, earth warming is not due to pollution.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.38,0:09:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to look, why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.68,0:09:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And we looked deeper, and we found, yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.34,0:09:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it's due to magnetic solar activity,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.18,0:09:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the magnetic radiation of the surface of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.34,0:10:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And our core drilling is down through 10,000 years
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.66,0:10:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't calibrate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.33,0:10:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, that hit the news this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.38,0:10:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So as of this week, I'm an OK person in the world again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.96,0:10:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.71,0:10:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to offend certain people, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.13,0:10:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So one of the reasons people have difficulty discerning truth
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.16,0:10:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and reality is there's so much investment
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.93,0:10:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in what they believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.11,0:10:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you want to stay free and become enlightened, don't pour
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.35,0:10:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of emotion into any view.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.62,0:10:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you don't have to die for environmentalism
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.03,0:10:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,or, you know what I mean, some particular viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.67,0:10:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It supersedes reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.41,0:10:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,People throw all this intense emotion
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.51,0:10:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,into what they believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.33,0:10:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's bad enough to even believe it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.07,0:11:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's even worse to throw a lot of emotion into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.67,0:11:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If Al Gore's book don't win, you're
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.13,0:11:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,going to die or kill yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.61,0:11:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You should bomb the Pentagon or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.76,0:11:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, be passionate for God, be passionate for God
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.40,0:11:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than political labeling and put on everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.52,0:11:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because everything that's political in today's world,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.76,0:11:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't mention anything but it's got a label.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.90,0:11:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then all the passion that goes with that label,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.14,0:11:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.52,0:11:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,One reason not to get so passionately committed,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.52,0:11:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is because if it's proven wrong, you look like an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.34,0:11:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.82,0:11:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the good news is that NBC News and all those now
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.75,0:11:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,agree with the old doc here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.27,0:11:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He was right all along, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.07,0:12:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,My god, I thought that would show him, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.12,0:12:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The octogenarians are going to start off with a bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.13,0:12:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we can calibrate the level
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.67,0:12:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of anything in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.17,0:12:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, only about a third, which I didn't know
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.91,0:12:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,when I first started all this, only about a third
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.31,0:12:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of the people in the United States are capable of doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.61,0:12:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,To get the correct answer, you yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.71,0:12:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,have to be calibrated over 200, which
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.77,0:12:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,means you're more interested in truth than in falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.48,0:12:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Only a third of the people in the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.24,0:12:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,are more interested in truth than in falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.23,0:12:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.49,0:12:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,More interested in being right than knowing what the truth is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.51,0:12:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's called narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.00,0:12:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.60,0:12:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So what distorts the capacity to perceive essence rather
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.34,0:12:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,than appearance is a detached commitment to truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.86,0:12:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach God through truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.48,0:13:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And the pathway through God, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.40,0:13:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,sort through everything ever written by man anywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.76,0:13:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in time and calibrate what's true and follow what's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.78,0:13:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll take you to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.92,0:13:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All truth will eventually take you to divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.81,0:13:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the source and the essence of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.31,0:13:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which arises truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.71,0:13:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you do nothing, every time you come to a split in the road,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.55,0:13:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you follow which one calibrates to the higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.91,0:13:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And you keep doing that, you'll end up God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.72,0:13:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth is a pathway to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.66,0:13:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotion, all these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.24,0:13:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.40,0:13:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But devotion can lead you astray, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.36,0:13:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,because people are devoted to Nazism,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.18,0:13:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,not devoted to all kinds of horrible things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.30,0:13:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotion to what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.56,0:13:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotion to truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.10,0:13:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So we call this the devotional nonduality.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.48,0:14:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonduality meaning you're beyond truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.72,0:14:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You find out what is the truth, and then you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.90,0:14:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,devote yourself to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.10,0:14:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So in your life, then, all you have to do is look up these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.69,0:14:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see those things that will bring you to God
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.13,0:14:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,are the highest, an inner joy, lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.19,0:14:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason precedes that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.11,0:14:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see that reason is beyond emotionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.22,0:14:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason doesn't have anything to do with emotionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.04,0:14:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer to a problem doesn't depend on how you feel about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.34,0:14:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.47,0:14:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.49,0:14:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So reason is in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.79,0:14:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still emotionality in the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.52,0:14:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And however, it's positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.80,0:14:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's positive, positive emotionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.44,0:14:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then below level 200, you have all the negatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.14,0:14:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,190 is pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.43,0:14:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.13,0:15:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And the blogs we get calibrate at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.18,0:15:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And those are like the guy who writes the books that disproves Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.25,0:15:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He's still writing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.01,0:15:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,How he explains the atomic bomb, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.68,0:15:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So pridefulness, then, is at about 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.12,0:15:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you get just hatefulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.30,0:15:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So then we get some blogs that are just, I hate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.70,0:15:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.58,0:15:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,At least he's honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.70,0:15:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Then people hate things and think they love them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.74,0:15:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.18,0:15:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just going to do a quick review.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.84,0:15:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the enlightened and divine states.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.10,0:15:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you see, the higher you get,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.64,0:15:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment really starts at 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.84,0:15:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's formally on that chart, 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.40,0:15:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's beyond the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.44,0:15:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is nonlinear as context rather than content.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.82,0:15:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you go all the way up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.10,0:16:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, you go on up to 1,000 in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.09,0:16:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you go up to infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.69,0:16:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where the numbers are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.83,0:16:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We had numbers here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.31,0:16:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangels at 60,000 and up, 6,000 and up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.27,0:16:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, what the calibrated level of consciousness does
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.29,0:16:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is confirm spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.55,0:16:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirm spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.35,0:16:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirm it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.05,0:16:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.57,0:16:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirms it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.91,0:16:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.07,0:16:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the distribution of the consciousness in the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.95,0:16:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You see approximately 80% of the world calibrates below 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.83,0:16:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,which explains the nature of the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.22,0:16:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, next.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.16,0:16:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So man is on an evolutionary pathway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.76,0:16:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So distribution of the levels of mankind, about 22% of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.60,0:17:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is above 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.46,0:17:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the great man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.30,0:17:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The mass of mankind is below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.32,0:17:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, truth does not prevail in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.31,0:17:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsehood prevails.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.31,0:17:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So why doesn't the world just destruct, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.57,0:17:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.17,0:17:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't destruct because those above 200, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.57,0:17:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is a logarithmic chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.19,0:17:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So the power of those above 200 is so enormous,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.93,0:17:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that it balances the approximate 80% below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.54,0:17:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A group like this, which we've calibrated a number of times,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.78,0:17:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is enormously powerful in balancing out these energies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.16,0:17:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So a group like this is right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.97,0:18:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And because their power is exponentially, logarithmically
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.25,0:18:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,very high, it counterbalances negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.39,0:18:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the negativity is very high.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.63,0:18:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very high.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.31,0:18:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They are greater in numbers, but their energy is far weaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.08,0:18:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So spiritual groups that are highly committed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.12,0:18:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,help maintain the energy level of mankind overall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.50,0:18:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.47,0:18:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And here is the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.03,0:18:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,over a timeline which you're going to have to throw out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.31,0:18:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it recently took a dip down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.11,0:18:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently took a dip down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.07,0:18:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness of mankind is is brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.87,0:18:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of just dropped five or seven points in Western civilization, in the U.S., and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.53,0:18:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world in general.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.07,0:18:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's make a note.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.65,0:18:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to repair that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.21,0:18:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to go like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.05,0:18:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't argue with God about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.12,0:19:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If he wants it to go like this, it'll go like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.80,0:19:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll go like that, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.56,0:19:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, this is just the evolution of the energy of life over great eons of time, great
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.59,0:19:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,eons of time, and you can't see it from back there, so we'll go on to the next one, and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.92,0:19:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that evolution through the animal kingdom, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.85,0:19:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine if this was a couple of million years ago, we'd be out there saying, save
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.80,0:19:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the dinosaurs, save Tyrannosaurus.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.16,0:19:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Alex, save Tyrannosaurus, Alex, save Tyrannosaurus, Alex, save Tyrannosaurus, Rex.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.02,0:19:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so adorable, so cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.76,0:19:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we see the evolution of mankind then through life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.56,0:20:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Life can only originate from life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.79,0:20:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No skeptic has ever been able to create life out of non-life, which is the downfall of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.97,0:20:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the materialistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.03,0:20:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The secularist is that life is a totally different energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.15,0:20:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It cannot arise from non-life, either organic or non-organic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.27,0:20:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So life originates from a different source than the material world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.37,0:20:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we see all the animals and all our favorites that we've talked about over the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.47,0:20:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,years, Komodo dragon and the octopus.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.06,0:20:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Octopus is extremely intelligent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.06,0:20:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It really should be more than 20.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.24,0:20:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't we pluck them up a little bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.44,0:20:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There was one on the octopus on TV the other night.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.30,0:20:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They're so smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.30,0:20:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just really brainy, you know, smarter than people, many often.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.23,0:20:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we go up through why dolphins calibrate different than whales.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.51,0:20:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.51,0:21:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Whales and dolphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.59,0:21:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I'll get an argument in the email.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.27,0:21:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.25,0:21:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.83,0:21:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask me how come.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.31,0:21:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.53,0:21:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we come up through the evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.31,0:21:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The evolution of the animals, animal kingdom, and you see the major shift at level 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.61,0:21:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,From the carnivore who lives by the death of others, eats others, to the herbivore, which
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.49,0:21:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes benign, so it's similar to our chart, 200 and up is benign, and less than 200 tends
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.19,0:21:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to be carnivorous, it'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.98,0:21:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we come up through all of our favorites.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.28,0:21:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.98,0:21:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something very special about dogs and family dogs and cats, because you see
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.12,0:21:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the cat's purr is at 500, and the dog's wagging tail is at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.93,0:22:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something very, very special about them, spiritually speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.00,0:22:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Their capacity to love, loyalty, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.38,0:22:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.04,0:22:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.58,0:22:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go on next.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.34,0:22:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.70,0:22:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we skip the negative and then we get up to low.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.14,0:22:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,level of truth, then we get up to the level of emotions, positive emotions, and then when
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.83,0:22:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we get to the consciousness level of the 400s, you leave the world of emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.41,0:22:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason and the intellect don't care how you feel about it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.67,0:22:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people try to mix the two, how they feel about facts and reality, and it's really irrelevant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.97,0:22:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,how you feel about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.95,0:22:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are the great books of the Western world, which are the foundation, the emergence
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.15,0:22:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Renaissance, the great intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.27,0:22:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really a rebirth of what went on in ancient Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.85,0:22:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The high point of human civilization was really in ancient Greece, then it fell apart, and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.84,0:23:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,then it was resurrected.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.98,0:23:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's so.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.98,0:23:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The high point of human evolution, we have a person that asked this, was the intellectual
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.37,0:23:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.57,0:23:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellectual world was the foundation.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.61,0:23:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellectual world was the ancient Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.67,0:23:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I was intuitive, but I never did the Aramon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.04,0:23:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So then it was reborn in the Renaissance, and now these are all called dead white men,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.36,0:23:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.40,0:23:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't allow them in the academia anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.58,0:23:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but this is the intellectual elegance all the way up to consciousness level 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.85,0:23:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,499 is the level of great geniuses, Sir Isaac Newton, Freud, Sir Isaac Newton, Freud,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.89,0:23:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,who else?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.89,0:23:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,499, Einstein, 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.31,0:24:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So 499 is as high as you can push the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.65,0:24:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have always had respect for this presentation of the development of the human intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.47,0:24:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.25,0:24:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.37,0:24:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That differentiates man from the animal, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.20,0:24:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, animals can hate and animals can love.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.60,0:24:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So what makes you different is that you have a prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.74,0:24:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.66,0:24:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of the prefrontal cortex is to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.90,0:24:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's work.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.40,0:24:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we talk about content.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.24,0:24:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's to the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.18,0:24:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And content, what does it look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.70,0:24:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends on the proximate context, the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.50,0:24:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.50,0:24:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time, he was intoxicated and the lady's dog was biting his leg and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.74,0:25:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So proximate context influences our understanding of what went on.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.82,0:25:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He shot her, but he was drunk and she was attacking him with a knife, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.90,0:25:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the proximate context.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.48,0:25:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the infinite context is consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.37,0:25:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth and understanding and reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.47,0:25:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the proximate context.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.47,0:25:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And understanding and reality is to interpret content within context.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.83,0:25:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So one of the easiest ways to lie in our society, and it's done all the time, is to just ignore
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.61,0:25:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.61,0:25:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignore the context, because that way you can make people wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.82,0:25:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you put it in the context, then you can't make them wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.12,0:25:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So you know, say we were at war at the time, oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.16,0:25:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we'll move on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.43,0:25:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This I just put on for, not that I understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.31,0:25:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But it sure looks impressive, don't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.90,0:25:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.18,0:26:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because quantum mechanics is in the linear domain or in the intellectual domain, coming
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.94,0:26:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,closer and closer to an understanding of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.04,0:26:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And Henry Stapp, whose book you can get off, you can get for free, Henry Stapp, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.96,0:26:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,print out his book for free, his most recent book, you know, brings an approximation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.00,0:26:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, what he's emphasizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.08,0:26:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And which I emphasize, is the effect of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.47,0:26:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The effect of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.59,0:26:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So we say that this world does not operate according to the Newtonian laws of causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.55,0:26:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of this causing of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.79,0:26:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, there is a potential, a potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.19,0:26:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And under the proper conditions, meaning the proper context, the potentiality emerges as
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.37,0:26:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,an actuality, not as a result of causation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.05,0:26:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So the little seed is not caused.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.37,0:26:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody forces it to grow into a blossom.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.37,0:27:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Under proper conditions, one of those being your intention for it to grow, the conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.55,0:27:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you add are warmth, and sunlight, and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.93,0:27:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, like a pupa coming out of a cocoon, it emerges as a flower or a butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.13,0:27:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But nobody forces it to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.17,0:27:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody causes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.63,0:27:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You can take a cocoon and squeeze it and apply all the force you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.79,0:27:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't create a butterfly, you'll just create a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.59,0:27:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So intention is very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.45,0:27:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you listen to the lecture with the intention
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.75,0:27:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of advancing your own level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.59,0:27:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and doing it communally with all of us together,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.31,0:27:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that is the likelihood that we'll develop, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.59,0:27:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So a group like this is very powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.54,0:27:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.02,0:27:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so as I say, you can get this for yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.72,0:27:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,happily, Henry Stapp, you can print it out for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.50,0:28:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go next.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.72,0:28:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the other difference that bothers people politically,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.56,0:28:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,everything bothers people politically,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.38,0:28:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the two levels, above and below 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.90,0:28:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,have a different brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.58,0:28:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This is profoundly important.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.96,0:28:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200 people process things.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.24,0:28:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Left brain dominance, completely differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.44,0:28:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They do it through the left side of the brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.22,0:28:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and these are the primarily animal responses.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.40,0:28:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal responses.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.14,0:28:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So things, this is how perception becomes distorted.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.55,0:28:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you perceive the world through the left brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.87,0:28:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200, you're seeing it more as an animal sees it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.93,0:28:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody agrees with you, they're a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.77,0:28:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If they don't agree with you, you're an enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.89,0:28:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and have to attack them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.25,0:29:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,People that don't like what we say here,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.97,0:29:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,read in the book, have a cup of whiskey and sodas,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.99,0:29:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,they sit down at the computer,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.02,0:29:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,F you, you dumb ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.64,0:29:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that what they say sometimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.96,0:29:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,She reads them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.28,0:29:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not allowed to read them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.83,0:29:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The office staff won't let me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.09,0:29:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, what's that there?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.03,0:29:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to see this.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.65,0:29:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so how does forgiveness come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.20,0:30:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgiveness is seeing error as limitation
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.12,0:30:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is a physiologic limitation
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.46,0:30:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,due to brain function itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.45,0:30:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what Jesus Christ said,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.09,0:30:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to forgive because people who are not integrous
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.85,0:30:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot help but be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.57,0:30:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Cannot help but be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.65,0:30:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So the forgiveness then,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.41,0:30:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,people say forgiving is very hard to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.65,0:30:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not hard once you understand this,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.91,0:30:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that the person is limited
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.07,0:30:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,by their own brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.07,0:30:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And from this side, out this end comes F you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.08,0:30:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We call a spade a spade in these lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.02,0:30:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And what did Jesus Christ say about them?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.28,0:30:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He said to avoid them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.72,0:31:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, don't attack evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.66,0:31:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid, do not become engaged with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.08,0:31:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not try to prove it that it's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.94,0:31:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go to war with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.22,0:31:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get into an argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.33,0:31:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw their emails away.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.06,0:31:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't answer anything that calibrates under 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.00,0:31:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They bring in a message and say it was a calibrative set.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.20,0:31:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's under 200, we just throw it in the waste basket.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.34,0:31:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens at consciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.34,0:31:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which one arise at through karmic advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.04,0:31:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and devotion, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.02,0:31:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,through prayer and through forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.99,0:31:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and through the mercy of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.44,0:31:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is now the brain shifts sides
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.64,0:31:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's the production of kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.69,0:32:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What shifts the brain chemistry from here to here
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.99,0:32:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is the emergence of kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.33,0:32:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And with kundalini energy emerges the etheric body,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.65,0:32:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the etheric brain, the etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.79,0:32:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So the processing that goes on here
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.85,0:32:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is instantaneous through the etheric brain
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.25,0:32:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,before it even gets to the prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.15,0:32:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, this person sees things differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.83,0:32:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the reasons they see things differently
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.01,0:32:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is because that's their intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.67,0:32:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I see things differently now is a stock phrase in 12-step groups
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.55,0:32:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of course of miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.80,0:32:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody spiritually devoted will eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.62,0:32:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to see things more benign and feel sorry for people
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.64,0:32:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than hate them, feel sorry for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.66,0:32:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't hate the Komodo dragon, but I don't step
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.54,0:32:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,into his cage in my bare feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.98,0:32:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So it doesn't mean to be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.72,0:32:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I think it's misinterpreted
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.62,0:33:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,as being stupid and tell you, oh, Komodo dragons,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.20,0:33:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,they won't hurt you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.06,0:33:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they're OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.68,0:33:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They're OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.78,0:33:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last thing they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.48,0:33:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So being blind to danger doesn't mean to be oblivious.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.02,0:33:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You can love the animal and not bother with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.72,0:33:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but I wouldn't get in the cage with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.56,0:33:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.81,0:33:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so below 200, then, you have a different,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.30,0:33:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a columnist named Pitts, and he coined the term, which
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.68,0:33:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I've quoted in the current book,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.54,0:33:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that these people on the left here
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.70,0:33:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,live in an alternate reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.24,0:33:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an alternate reality, and it's a different reality
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.72,0:33:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,from this level here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.18,0:33:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,One reason it's different, it literally is.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.32,0:33:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Pitts was right, even though he's a columnist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.74,0:33:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They actually have a different reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.82,0:33:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They process things differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.42,0:34:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They see them differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.78,0:34:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They experience them differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.25,0:34:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here, you experience things more.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.11,0:34:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He's more benign, above 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.64,0:34:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So if something is destructive, out of respect,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.84,0:34:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,out of respect for his reality, I don't provoke it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.17,0:34:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.49,0:34:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I respect the Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.65,0:34:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't make them wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.09,0:34:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't hate them, but I respect them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.26,0:34:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So unfortunately, sometimes idealism
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.68,0:34:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,reaches the point of being the fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.18,0:34:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking that you can ignore the reality of what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.94,0:34:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see that's disrespectful?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.41,0:34:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't think certain people in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.29,0:34:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,are out to kill you, you're not being respectful
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.23,0:34:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of their belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.03,0:34:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I believe the international problems we have
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.49,0:34:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is a failure to not only to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.85,0:35:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that different viewpoint, but to give it due respect,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.75,0:35:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to give it due respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.49,0:35:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody is carrying a loaded 45,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.09,0:35:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't stick your fingers in his arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.33,0:35:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He's always, that's disrespectful.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.66,0:35:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.53,0:35:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So I believe in respecting one's energies.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.29,0:35:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Your biggest safeguard is your respect for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.57,0:35:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because out of respect, then you feel
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.21,0:35:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,obligated to understand them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.05,0:35:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you understand them, you're not so likely
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.51,0:35:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to stumble into offending.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.97,0:35:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.24,0:35:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,God versus science.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.58,0:35:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how this got in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.91,0:35:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We did God versus science.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.61,0:35:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't need to do that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.82,0:35:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.22,0:35:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here we are at today.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.74,0:35:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew we'd get to today somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.18,0:35:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What is real?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.08,0:35:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What is real?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.34,0:36:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody thinks their mind knows what is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.74,0:36:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to do that next lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.74,0:36:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is real?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.90,0:36:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought we'll start with just simple definitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.86,0:36:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What is real?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.24,0:36:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, there's a definition.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.78,0:36:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We say, well, it's actual.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.40,0:36:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.10,0:36:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.64,0:36:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And mainly what we say is real is physical.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.60,0:36:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I really have 10 toes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.82,0:36:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, really have.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.44,0:36:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I had 10 toes in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.52,0:36:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it's within the linear domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.00,0:36:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's linear, it can be confirmed by the senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.22,0:36:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So even the animal is capable of material linear reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.82,0:36:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fox can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.18,0:36:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the hare.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.90,0:36:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's confirmable by the senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.19,0:37:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you only need your left brain animal world to see whether a thing is in reality factual.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.47,0:37:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That is manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.90,0:37:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we jump to the next level from just sensory confirmation, the fox sees the rabbit there,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.56,0:37:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to mentalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.33,0:37:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And we run into the world of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.73,0:37:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In science, for a thing to be real, it has to be, or true, it has to be measurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.11,0:37:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Some, you know, it has to have dimensions, and it must exist somewhere in time and space.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.24,0:37:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, science is not really capable of dealing with the abstract.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.69,0:37:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that? All the answers to life will not come out of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.85,0:37:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The world that we deal with is adequately described by science,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.71,0:37:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,with its advance now to quantum mechanics and the Heisenberg principle,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.71,0:37:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it enlarges its realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.71,0:37:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the current view of the universe is that the universe is held in place
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.97,0:38:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.26,0:38:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's consciousness itself that holds this world in its present state.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.26,0:38:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Without consciousness, the universe would not exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.54,0:38:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So all, as you read in Stapp's newest book,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.54,0:38:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole universe exists
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.54,0:38:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,within consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.54,0:38:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,within consciousness and because of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.70,0:38:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you look at a thing, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.70,0:38:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you have delay going from potentiality to actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.93,0:38:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,By observation, you block the collapse of the wave function.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.21,0:38:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So the universe is suspended between potentiality and actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.21,0:38:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because we've collapsed the wave function at its present level, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.55,0:38:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all incorrect scientifically, so we'll forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.87,0:38:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What is real is confirmable by the senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.87,0:39:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Science then measures things via information about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.87,0:39:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,such as measurement, time and place.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.87,0:39:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you look at, when you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.03,0:39:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I think a thing is real,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.03,0:39:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you've really drawn a mental conclusion of your sensory experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.03,0:39:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's really the lower mind in the animal that says it's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.03,0:39:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal doesn't have to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.88,0:39:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in, within you is an animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.88,0:39:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, within every human there's the animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.88,0:39:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's your animal that says the thing is real.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.88,0:39:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch, oh, oh, that's a stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.88,0:39:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It says it's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.88,0:39:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What it means is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.88,0:39:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's a subjective based on faith in sensory input.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.26,0:39:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What you say is real is based on your faith
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.26,0:39:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,on your sensory input.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.87,0:39:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's therefore a subjective statement based on faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.87,0:40:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, knocking faith means you would have no way
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.51,0:40:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of knowing anything about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.51,0:40:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You have faith in your own sensory experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.51,0:40:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And throughout evolution then,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.54,0:40:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we've developed the capacity to be able to sense
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.58,0:40:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the linear domain in a group.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.58,0:40:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great level.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.61,0:40:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's also prone to errors we'll get to later.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.73,0:40:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I am is provisional to consciousness levels above 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.79,0:40:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a mystification that people themselves are limited
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.79,0:40:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in their level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.05,0:40:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200 they exist and they are sensory,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.05,0:40:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but they are unaware of their existence as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.50,0:40:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't say I exist, it just is.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.92,0:40:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.92,0:40:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.92,0:41:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't realize the value of life as a gift,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.18,0:41:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as existence itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.18,0:41:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,then you don't value it in others.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.18,0:41:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see cultures that destroy life of others
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.43,0:41:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,because they themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.43,0:41:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,although they exist as an animal,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.43,0:41:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not really aware of their existence as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.46,0:41:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the sensory world is based on interpretation of data.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.90,0:41:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The argument about what's real
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.90,0:41:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's not,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.90,0:41:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll run it through again when we get to what's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.90,0:41:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And we did run through it once before
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.90,0:41:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,when we talked about relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.90,0:41:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the intellectual problem is,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.90,0:41:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Pythagoras, as reported in Plato,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.41,0:41:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,says,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.76,0:41:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the world I experience is real to me
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.50,0:42:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and the world that you experience is real to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.62,0:42:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.62,0:42:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no absolute reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.68,0:42:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All reality is only subjective,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.22,0:42:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,which is really the basis of solipsism,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.42,0:42:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that the way I experience the world is my world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.42,0:42:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it ends up with,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.86,0:42:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,actually, the intellectual argument,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.86,0:42:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,philosophic argument,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.37,0:42:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,ends up with an absurdity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.66,0:42:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,because the fact that you say you exist and I exist
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.14,0:42:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean that neither one of us does.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.10,0:42:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There are two, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.06,0:42:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates, of course, then brought this further
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.06,0:42:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and pointed out how illusion is perceived as a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.06,0:42:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And Socrates is a great friend to spiritual students
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.06,0:42:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because he gives you an avenue
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.06,0:43:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,by which forgiveness comes about through understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.47,0:43:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you forgive people
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.47,0:43:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because, as Socrates said,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.47,0:43:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,illusion, then, is your perception of reality
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.86,0:43:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's projected out into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.86,0:43:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What you want, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.98,0:43:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What you desire, you see as the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.98,0:43:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the trouble is you cannot see truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.98,0:43:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And this was further elaborated, of course, by Descartes,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.05,0:43:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,who pointed out, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.05,0:43:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,there's the world within
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.05,0:43:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there's the world without
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.05,0:43:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and the comprehension of reality
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.05,0:43:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,depends, then, on transcending that duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.05,0:43:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the only way to transcend these dualities
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.05,0:43:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,pointed out throughout time
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.05,0:43:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,from Jesus Christ on through Socrates, Descartes, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.05,0:43:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or Protagoras,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.01,0:43:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the only way to transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.01,0:43:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the possibility of making an error
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.39,0:44:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,about reality or truth
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.39,0:44:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is, frankly, consciousness calibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.39,0:44:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There's absolutely...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.65,0:44:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,man has never, until now, evolved a way
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.65,0:44:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to transcend that duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.65,0:44:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.65,0:44:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.97,0:44:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All of mankind's history,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.97,0:44:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,he's never been able to discern
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.97,0:44:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,essence from appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.48,0:44:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, we have a very simple scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.50,0:44:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like he never could tell altitude
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.50,0:44:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,until somebody discovered an altimeter
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.50,0:44:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and now it's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.50,0:44:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we don't have any opinion or view on things.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.50,0:44:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We just calibrate what is the level of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.50,0:44:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the essence of that which is being described.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.50,0:44:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can be completely determined
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.50,0:44:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and detached from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.17,0:44:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, what we think is real
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.17,0:44:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is a sensory and a mental presumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.90,0:44:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we have a review of what I just said.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.90,0:44:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe is purely a mentalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.90,0:44:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no out there, only in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.90,0:45:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.90,0:45:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no you and then the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.82,0:45:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how do you prove what's real?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.82,0:45:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's through consensual validation.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.82,0:45:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If I say a thing weighs so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.82,0:45:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you weigh it and you get the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.82,0:45:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,then we both agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.82,0:45:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't create a reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.82,0:45:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but that creates an agreement
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.82,0:45:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,on what both of us presumed to be a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.82,0:45:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Still does not tell you what's real,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.82,0:45:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but it tells you what is confirmable
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.82,0:45:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,within the usual definition of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.46,0:45:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next slide?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.13,0:45:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so what we did now
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.38,0:45:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is review up to the present time
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.38,0:45:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we just got through saying
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.70,0:45:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,reality is subjective
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.70,0:45:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,based on faith in one's senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.70,0:45:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's experiential of one's senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.70,0:46:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, an animal is capable
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.70,0:46:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of discerning what's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.70,0:46:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't discern what's truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.70,0:46:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but he gets what's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.82,0:46:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's dependent on the reliability
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.82,0:46:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of the information that your senses are giving you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.82,0:46:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, it's actually a testimonial.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.30,0:46:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All statements about reality
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.10,0:46:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,are a testimonial.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.10,0:46:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to get somebody else
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.30,0:46:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to get rid of their argument,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.30,0:46:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,just say, call it,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.30,0:46:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just a testimonial.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.62,0:46:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a testimonial.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.62,0:46:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We all say that it fulfills
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.40,0:46:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the criteria of facts,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.40,0:46:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which is reliable data.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.40,0:46:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To know what is real
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.66,0:46:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is a subjective presumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.72,0:46:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's mind says,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.72,0:46:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I know what's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.72,0:46:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.72,0:46:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've become more
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.72,0:46:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or a little humble, more humble,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.72,0:46:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,when we realize that that's the presumption
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.72,0:46:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that this mind is making now.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.82,0:47:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And we always leave room
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.82,0:47:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,for correction later.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.94,0:47:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So a sophisticated spiritual student
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.58,0:47:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,drops a lot of their narcissism
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.58,0:47:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and instead takes on a certain humility
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.61,0:47:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that whatever I think and believe now
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.61,0:47:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,could change later
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.61,0:47:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,because additional information comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.61,0:47:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So as spiritually committed people,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.90,0:47:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we tend to be somewhat more humble
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.90,0:47:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,about our statements about the world
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.96,0:47:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and know that it's subject
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.96,0:47:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to editing later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.96,0:47:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How many planets are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.82,0:47:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there were nine,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.82,0:47:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and now there's eight, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.82,0:47:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're somewhat humble then.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.69,0:47:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So intellectual humility
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.75,0:47:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,then serves
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.75,0:47:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritual purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.75,0:47:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're not so dead sure
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.75,0:48:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're absolutely right
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.75,0:48:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,about everything all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.75,0:48:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a likelihood, a presumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.75,0:48:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So all information then
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.75,0:48:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in a spiritual context
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.75,0:48:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is held as presumptive,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.75,0:48:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's only provable
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.88,0:48:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,by actually becoming,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.88,0:48:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,by actually becoming.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.88,0:48:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Fulfills properties of content, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.66,0:48:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.66,0:48:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's time for a break?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.66,0:48:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.78,0:48:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.78,0:48:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll finish up this slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.64,0:48:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,To know what is real
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.64,0:48:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is a subject of resumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.64,0:48:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, with humility,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.64,0:48:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so we talk about humility
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.64,0:48:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.64,0:48:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality means an openness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.64,0:48:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to receive.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.64,0:48:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I've often said,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.64,0:48:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it's yin in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.64,0:48:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's yin in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.70,0:48:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And certainty is like yang.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.70,0:48:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know that,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.70,0:48:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know that,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.70,0:48:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know that,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.70,0:48:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and no worth warming
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.70,0:48:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is up to evil Americans at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.70,0:49:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's very yang.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.70,0:49:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't leave any room
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.70,0:49:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to back off gracefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.09,0:49:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Tentative means,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.09,0:49:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.09,0:49:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,even now,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.09,0:49:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.09,0:49:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that the temperature variation
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.22,0:49:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.22,0:49:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is likely due
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.22,0:49:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to the magnetic activity
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.22,0:49:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of the surface of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.22,0:49:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But even now,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.50,0:49:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't say it's certain,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.50,0:49:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,even though it's been
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.50,0:49:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,scientifically proven.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.50,0:49:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I say it's likely,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.50,0:49:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because that could change
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.50,0:49:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,tomorrow, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.50,0:49:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't want to catch
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.86,0:49:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in all our chips,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.86,0:49:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.86,0:49:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Vegas of spiritual work,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.86,0:49:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't put all your chips
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.86,0:49:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,on one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.86,0:49:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.92,0:49:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,To know what is real
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.92,0:49:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is, therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.92,0:49:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a subjective presumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.92,0:49:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's best not to invest
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.92,0:49:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,narcissistic emotionality into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.92,0:49:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Look how difficult it is
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.92,0:49:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to get off a position
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.92,0:49:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,when you've poured
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.92,0:50:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of emotional energy into it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.92,0:50:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and become sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.92,0:50:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a fanatic about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.92,0:50:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why people
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.92,0:50:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,just can't have a view
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.92,0:50:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,about a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.92,0:50:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,without becoming maniacal about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.92,0:50:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.92,0:50:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to change
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.92,0:50:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a little thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.92,0:50:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,they have a whole parade,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.92,0:50:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.92,0:50:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and what are they going to have,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.92,0:50:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a summit aid or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.92,0:50:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,People are out there
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.92,0:50:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with parades
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.92,0:50:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and all kinds of...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.92,0:50:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's all the emotion about?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.92,0:50:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why contaminate,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.11,0:50:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.11,0:50:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the intellectual world
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.11,0:50:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with emotion?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.46,0:50:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.71,0:50:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to know what is real
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.71,0:50:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is a subjective presumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.71,0:50:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And with humility,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.71,0:50:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,we say it's a likelihood.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.97,0:50:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And all we're talking about anyway
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.97,0:50:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is content.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.97,0:50:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And what it really means,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.97,0:50:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,we haven't even gotten to it yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.97,0:50:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because what it means
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.97,0:50:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is signified as
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.97,0:50:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a consequence of context.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.10,0:50:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a product
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.10,0:50:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of the sensory world,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.10,0:50:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the animal world.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.10,0:50:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you add human mental processing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.10,0:50:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and editing.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.10,0:51:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.35,0:51:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,all information is itself
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.35,0:51:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,only tentative and provisional.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.35,0:51:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything I say today
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.35,0:51:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is tentative and provisional.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.35,0:51:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the best understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.35,0:51:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that I have at the moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.35,0:51:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.35,0:51:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,To think you know
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.35,0:51:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is a narcissistic premise.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.35,0:51:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.35,0:51:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you know about,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.35,0:51:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you can know about a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.35,0:51:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way to know a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.35,0:51:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.57,0:51:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The only one who knows
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.57,0:51:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is to be a cat
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.57,0:51:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.08,0:51:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only one
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.08,0:51:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,who knows what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.08,0:51:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a cat
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.08,0:51:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.08,0:51:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only one
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.08,0:51:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,who knows
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.08,0:51:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.37,0:51:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a cat
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.37,0:51:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.37,0:51:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only one
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.37,0:51:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,who knows
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.37,0:51:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is to be a cat
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.37,0:51:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.37,0:51:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You can know about a cat,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.37,0:51:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but you cannot know.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.62,0:51:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,To actually know
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.62,0:51:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.62,0:51:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.52,0:51:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And this brings us
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.52,0:51:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to a very sophisticated
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.52,0:51:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,philosophic
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.52,0:51:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and metaphysical understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.52,0:51:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That reality
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.52,0:51:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is identity
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.52,0:51:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than description.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.52,0:51:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.13,0:51:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we run into
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.13,0:52:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,a political problem
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.13,0:52:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.26,0:52:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.26,0:52:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,what a thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.26,0:52:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than
