Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.65,1:03:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you calibrate why is it they can't do it,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.21,1:03:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you get because they're actually atheists.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.91,1:03:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you negate truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.27,1:03:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,then you don't have the privilege of access to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.29,1:03:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you negate truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.67,1:03:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then you lose the capacity to discern truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.00,1:03:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.87,1:03:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, we're negating all these various pathways
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.83,1:03:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to knowingness through the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.86,1:03:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,through what you think is real, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.20,1:03:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And next time we'll get to what people think is truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.60,1:03:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And you end up with a condition known as divine stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.18,1:04:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, divine stupidity is much to be desired.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.48,1:04:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember ending up in divine stupidity myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.87,1:04:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, in the spiritual traditional literature,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.36,1:04:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it's described as a state.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.84,1:04:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Divine stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.76,1:04:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I, myself, know nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.39,1:04:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Because whatever you think is a definition,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.13,1:04:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,all definitions are not factual.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.93,1:04:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.74,1:04:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What you are is sufficient statement
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.20,1:04:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,about which you say nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.93,1:04:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You no longer say I am this or I am that or this is that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.23,1:04:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You experience like the cat does.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.58,1:04:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you are, you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.82,1:04:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.15,1:04:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you can say about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.48,1:04:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So you end up with divine stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.13,1:05:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure if you asked Ramana Maharshi what he thought
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.47,1:05:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,about something, he'd tell you he had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.79,1:05:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you give up those little thought bundles.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.40,1:05:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And because you see them, that they're just thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.68,1:05:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're evanescent, and that they have no intrinsic reality
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.28,1:05:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,other than the belief.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.66,1:05:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the only reason you believe this sensory information is
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.38,1:05:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because you have faith in God.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.36,1:05:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You have faith in belief that they're telling you what's true,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.22,1:05:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're telling you what's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.51,1:05:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So you end up then with divine stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.19,1:05:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, the more lectures you attend, the dumber you will get.
