Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.79,1:11:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So then, it's subject to the context.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.33,1:11:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, spiritual, we, these are what are real to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.60,1:11:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Is faith, hope, devotion, prayer, commitment, devotion, those are real.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.96,1:11:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Those, of course, are all intangible, not provable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.86,1:11:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So to disparage them is because people are coming from the wrong realm.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.88,1:12:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,These can either be proven or disproven.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.76,1:12:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I say, the skeptic ridicules faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.07,1:12:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And has tremendous faith in his skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.11,1:12:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He lives and dies by his skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.31,1:12:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, has he got faith, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.43,1:12:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to kick this big rigmarole he writes about faith, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.11,1:12:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's a bigger sucker for faith than the skeptic, you know, the cynic.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.90,1:12:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.14,1:12:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So these states to divine idiocy, divine stupidity, go through humility.
