Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.31,1:13:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.26,1:13:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It tries to extract experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.86,1:13:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the way it's going to survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.87,1:13:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So enlightenment is when your awareness, when your observation gets beyond experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.30,1:13:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The leading edge of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.32,1:13:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiencer takes place in one ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.18,1:13:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Within one ten-thousandth of a second, the mind has already interpreted the incoming stimulus.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.37,1:14:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It jumps in there and categorizes it, makes it right, makes it wrong, makes it attractive, has an aversion.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.53,1:14:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,To get beyond the experiencer, just to the witness observer,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.99,1:14:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,just to witness and observe without necessarily extracting experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.93,1:14:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.93,1:14:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the experiencer is the leading edge of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.00,1:14:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So meditative and contemplative, then, is to be with consciousness-awareness without
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.04,1:14:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,necessarily experiencing the content of consciousness-awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.59,1:14:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds tricky, but one time it suddenly comes to you that one is the witness of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.87,1:14:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,one is the observer.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.87,1:14:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.47,1:14:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't necessarily have to experience it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.29,1:14:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to juice it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.00,1:14:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego, to survive, is addicted to experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.68,1:15:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And it survives because of the juice it gets out of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.46,1:15:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So we eventually transcend that through faith, hope, devotion, and prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.24,1:15:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, please take me, help me go beyond that.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.38,1:15:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Through humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.38,1:15:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Through self-realization and awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.20,1:15:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Through mindfulness.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.63,1:15:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We get to the observer-witness.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.56,1:15:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not difficult to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.06,1:15:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That can be done.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.99,1:15:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And because we notice that below the thinking mind, there is a silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.53,1:15:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you focus on the silence, you'll notice that your mind isn't saying anything about
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.53,1:15:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what's going on out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.80,1:15:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego jumps in, tries to fill it up with something.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.60,1:15:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you lose your attraction to the titillation and novelty of the mind's thinkingness, trying
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.41,1:16:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to extract experiencing, you'd be satisfied with having no experience, thoughts, feelings,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.01,1:16:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.01,1:16:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of you say, well, what do you feel about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.14,1:16:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any feeling about it at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.16,1:16:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Feeling about what?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.16,1:16:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's coming to an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.16,1:16:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's coming to an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.16,1:16:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.16,1:16:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what do you know about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.16,1:16:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not to allow.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.16,1:16:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not to allow.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.24,1:16:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not to allow.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.37,1:16:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not to allow.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.97,1:16:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not to allow.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.09,1:16:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not to allow.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.11,1:16:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,SKYPETS
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.71,1:16:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's coming to an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.65,1:16:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Alcohol is coming to an end, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.65,1:16:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's coming to an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.77,1:16:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,God's coming to an end anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.89,1:16:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a year before 12 anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.99,1:16:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,December 21, 2012.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.03,1:16:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay your bills before then.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.12,1:16:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's always coming to the end.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.90,1:16:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always a guy on the sidewalk with a sandwich board.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.15,1:16:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Repent.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.15,1:16:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is coming to an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.45,1:16:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fact that he comes from the Mayan calendar doesn't give it any more truth than
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.19,1:16:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it does.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.27,1:17:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,firm people. I mean, the world is coming to an end in the year 2012. Oh boy. I got a whole
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.67,1:17:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,refrigerator full of pickled herring and I want to eat it. Cramming them down. And then you get
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.56,1:17:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to December 22nd, 2012, and you're not dead. You think, Christ, I ate up all the pickled herring.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.62,1:17:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Spent all my money. Oh, so if the world doesn't come to an end, that's what you got to worry
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.50,1:17:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,about. If the world comes to an end, you'll have no problems. If the world's not coming to an end,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.52,1:17:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,worry about that. Actually, it doesn't make any difference. So all right. So humility then
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.48,1:17:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and mindfulness, you become aware of what your mind is doing. It's always anticipating the future,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.80,1:18:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to get one up on the future, and clinging to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.12,1:18:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And to the past. So therefore, the present moment is ignored because your mind is either clinging to
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.58,1:18:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what just happened, trying to juice it, or it's anticipating what might happen, whether we're all
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.52,1:18:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,going to expire in 2021, for instance. So these eventually lead you through mindfulness then,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.41,1:18:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,through divine stupidity, and through choice, then reflection and meditation,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.02,1:18:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm describing become common. The mind generally focuses on the small self, the ego, on gain,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.85,1:18:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,desire, accepting and rejecting. I like and I don't like. I like and I don't like. I like it and I don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.50,1:18:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody say, what do you think of that movie? Frankly, I don't think about it at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.37,1:19:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, I don't think about it. All right. So these character traits carry you this.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.81,1:19:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Perseverance.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.61,1:19:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Perseverance and commitment and acceptance. And the power of declaration, which we haven't spoken about yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.66,1:19:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There is intention. And then there is something beyond even intention that activates intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.78,1:19:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is to make a declaration and then live by the declaration.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.26,1:19:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people have made a declaration about the purpose of their life?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.10,1:19:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow. Quite a few. All right. Pretty sophisticated group.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.10,1:19:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It is.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.10,1:19:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,To declare that one is the servant of God and that one's purpose is to realize the divinity of one's own inner self
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.26,1:19:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the divinity of Almighty God and to become one with God.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.26,1:20:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a declaration made by, hmm, I hate to ask the number,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.83,1:20:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,declaration made by less than a half of one percent of humanity, less than a quarter of a percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.93,1:20:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A fraction. It's really a fraction of one percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.93,1:20:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever reached the evolution of consciousness where they make a declaration that the meaning and purpose of my life
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.93,1:20:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is to serve God, to become one with God, to become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.93,1:20:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we said, I think in power versus force, the number of people interested in reaching enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.09,1:20:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is less than one in ten million. You know, what do you want to do here in this world?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.50,1:20:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are the spiritual options.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.50,1:20:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So life in this world is purgatorial in my view of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.50,1:20:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Purgatorial. You don't have to worry about purgatory later. You're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.38,1:20:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing purgatory? You suffer out bad karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.38,1:21:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have the option to choose options for good karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.38,1:21:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that all purgatory is? So why be afraid of purgatory?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.54,1:21:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.54,1:21:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, if breaking your ankle doesn't hurt, then you'd be in a different place.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.60,1:21:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In this realm, purgatory, if you break your ankle, it hurts.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.60,1:21:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. So, in a celestial realm, you don't have any ankle to break.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.06,1:21:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that negativity means this, in this world, people bemoan it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.06,1:21:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to repeat, this is not a celestial realm. This is not a celestial realm.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.06,1:21:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,As a realm, my inner experience of it, however, can be heavenly.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.06,1:21:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, by perseverance, by acceptance, by declaration.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.22,1:21:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, declaration is very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.22,1:22:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If you declare who you are and the purpose of your life,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.34,1:22:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you've made a very major impact on what your consciousness is going to be attracted to.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.76,1:22:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be attracted to those things that bring about enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.76,1:22:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's going to be not attracted.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.82,1:22:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean, does not mean to have an aversion.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.82,1:22:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,An aversion is something different.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.20,1:22:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It means you're not attracted to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.20,1:22:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm differentiating.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.06,1:22:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,To not be attracted is different than aversion.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.06,1:22:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Because aversion, like attraction, is a trap.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.29,1:22:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,To have neither attraction nor diversion.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.29,1:22:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But just have no interest in a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.35,1:22:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's lots of movies that come up and are popular and lots of things on television and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.48,1:22:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That I just don't have an interest in.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.48,1:22:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I just say, I'm not really interested in that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.48,1:22:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was 22, I would have been.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.48,1:22:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God for old age, I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.48,1:23:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It solves a lot of problems, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.34,1:23:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't remember who you were mad at.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.34,1:23:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I was mad at somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.30,1:23:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't remember what I was mad at about.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.30,1:23:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I was mad at about something.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.30,1:23:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of consciousness, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.04,1:23:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is how you're going to experience the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.04,1:23:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you see you do with your personal experience
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.04,1:23:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is what you see happening in society
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.04,1:23:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is to dramatize the story into a narrative.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.04,1:23:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually a poor me or a bad you narrative.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.03,1:23:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a way of describing things now coming out of relativity.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.45,1:23:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no descriptions of relativity.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.45,1:23:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only narratives.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.45,1:23:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There are only narratives.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.45,1:24:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the story that your mind makes up about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.45,1:24:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, the dramatization of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.45,1:24:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,To make a bigger impact on others.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.54,1:24:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All of this comes out of meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.54,1:24:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What does a thing mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.57,1:24:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll get more into that next time.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.57,1:24:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning cannot be understood without context.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.57,1:24:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the cynic, you know, can't get anywhere with reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.60,1:24:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.14,1:24:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What he doesn't see is that it's the meaning,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.14,1:24:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the significance, the implication,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.18,1:24:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the non-linear, non-languaged understanding and comprehension.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.62,1:24:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So all spiritual understanding is revealed in its abstract meaning,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.52,1:24:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which you have an interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.52,1:24:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Use various adjectives, inferences, connotations, attitudes, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.52,1:24:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But those are all elaborations.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.74,1:25:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't just what happens, the significance, the content, the context.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.74,1:25:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But what is the meaning of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.74,1:25:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So you could take all of life and you say,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.74,1:25:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What is interesting about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.74,1:25:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing's really interesting about it except what it means.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.97,1:25:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's lacking meaning, then it's just a passing animal experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.97,1:25:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal sees a rubber ball go by.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.97,1:25:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He sees a cat go by.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.97,1:25:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But he doesn't get any meaning out of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.97,1:25:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning, what is the meaning?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.06,1:25:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So our significance then arises from our meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.06,1:25:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of our existence?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.06,1:25:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of our existence?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.06,1:25:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the value of existence itself?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.06,1:25:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it so great to even be a human being?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.06,1:25:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be better to be a kitty and just purr all day.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.58,1:25:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,See a dog and wag its tail and be happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.73,1:25:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.91,1:25:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind's proclivity for error.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.91,1:25:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We got one more slide after this?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.30,1:25:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.30,1:26:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Go faster.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.30,1:26:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind's proclivity for error.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.30,1:26:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We mentioned that 50% of blog sites are fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.74,1:26:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't write me an angry hot letter tonight.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.47,1:26:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 50% of the information in blogger land is fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.47,1:26:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 50% of all that bloggerism is fallacious to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.47,1:26:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to mention its intent, which is often vicious, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.81,1:26:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is about what you would expect.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.86,1:26:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in law courts, you'll find out there's a 50% error in lineup identifications.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.35,1:26:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, these are the possible suspects.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.35,1:26:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the man you saw on the street?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.35,1:26:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,50% error.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.64,1:27:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw the crime committed by a guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.89,1:27:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he this one, this one, this one, this one?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.89,1:27:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He's this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.40,1:27:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,50% likelihood that they will be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.40,1:27:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How many guys in the...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.88,1:27:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatchamacallit project have been released from prison?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.88,1:27:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that called?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.20,1:27:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mercy Project or something?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.20,1:27:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget how many.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.09,1:27:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,90 of them, at least, on death row.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.09,1:27:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when the DNA came out, they found that they were on death row, that they were actually innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.09,1:27:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And most of them were convicted due to a false identification.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.31,1:27:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you can't even believe your eyes, well, can you believe?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.82,1:27:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Even your eyes lie to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.82,1:27:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Even your eyes lie to you 50-50.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.82,1:27:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And bloggerdom is 50-50.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.82,1:27:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to happen to mankind?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.82,1:28:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Buried by bloggerism.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.23,1:28:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Death by bloggerism.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.23,1:28:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No, go to number four.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.80,1:28:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean the next, last one.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.06,1:28:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.06,1:28:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Death by bloggerism.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.06,1:28:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the decline of consciousness of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.06,1:28:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We went from 207 back down to 204.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.11,1:28:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the decline of consciousness level of the Western world, which is currently in free fall.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.21,1:28:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And the decline of consciousness level in America itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.34,1:28:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So, America went from 426 to 421.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.37,1:28:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind went back down.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.43,1:28:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He went from 190 to 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.43,1:28:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he went to 207.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.43,1:28:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he's back down to 204.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.43,1:28:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Western world is also declining.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.43,1:28:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.87,1:28:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we can't see what's real is because of bias.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.87,1:28:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the negativity of the intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.87,1:29:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of how you're aligned.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.16,1:29:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That determines your preferences.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.16,1:29:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And that determines your attractions and your aversions.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.16,1:29:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I always think if people don't like the things I say, please don't read the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.35,1:29:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Who asked you to read the book?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.35,1:29:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It says Dio on the first page and he's offended because you're defending God.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.35,1:29:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you read the first page, you idiot?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.01,1:29:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the intention to disparage truth, divinity, etc. blinds people.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.09,1:29:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And they end up writing the dumb blogs at 1 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.95,1:29:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Naivete. What is real?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.95,1:29:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Naivete is another downside.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.95,1:29:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's overcome by familiarity, interpretation, sophistication.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.95,1:29:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So many objections.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.95,1:29:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Many objections to truth are really facetious.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.34,1:30:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And every once in a while we'll get one.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.34,1:30:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just plain facetious.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.34,1:30:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Facetious.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.34,1:30:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.59,1:30:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Facetious.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.59,1:30:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And understanding is also reflective of intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.45,1:30:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Intelligence is an overall state.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.45,1:30:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just one's IQ.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.45,1:30:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Intelligence operationally depends on your education.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.45,1:30:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How you've been indoctrinated.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.45,1:30:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How you've been programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.45,1:30:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you've had the good fortune to have been brought up in a family that respects morality, ethics, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.45,1:30:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you're going to be more aware of when it's out.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.67,1:30:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Social influence, cultural norms, and expectations depend on many factors.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.67,1:30:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You see people think, oh, how wonderful my mind is.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.67,1:30:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what you're thinking has to do with how you were brought up.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.67,1:30:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Has to do with your neuronal connections.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.67,1:31:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Has to do with the social class, your sex, your gender.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.95,1:31:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Political indoctrination, the way you're brought up.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.95,1:31:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Has to do with the way things are labeled.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.02,1:31:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Depends on whether they're popular.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.02,1:31:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And not all depends on the media hype and the glamour.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.24,1:31:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What is truth in today's world is what people believe because it has been pounded into your head via the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.37,1:31:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Repetitious memes reappear, reappear, reappear.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.37,1:31:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, what people believe is true is how they've been indoctrinated.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.37,1:31:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultural norms and expectations.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.88,1:31:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Labeling, popularity, and how much media hype it gets.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.88,1:31:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in today's world, for media hype, people will sell anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.20,1:31:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Will they not?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.46,1:31:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Nude pictures of themselves or the most god awful information about their life.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.46,1:31:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it gets you on the daily news.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.46,1:31:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I feel sorry for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.52,1:32:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel sorry for the people who become victims.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.52,1:32:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you can see they're victims not only of their own egotism, but of all their controllers.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.52,1:32:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All the people who are getting multi-millions, feeding dispersion to the dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.55,1:32:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So they really get fed to the dogs for a price.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.55,1:32:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And those are the social influences.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.38,1:32:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.38,1:32:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how things change.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.38,1:32:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're active.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.38,1:32:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.38,1:32:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you inspect things.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.38,1:32:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you enjoy them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.38,1:32:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.38,1:32:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Find fault with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.38,1:32:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Criticize them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.38,1:32:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Or want to destroy them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.54,1:32:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So these all are values coming out of intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.67,1:32:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're trying to extract the truth about something, your intention about it is already interpreting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.67,1:32:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So some of the funny blogs we get, or one of those things you get on the internet machine,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.67,1:32:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with the person's intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.67,1:33:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,To become facetious in order to ridicule something.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.77,1:33:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see the departure from truth and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.77,1:33:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,On top of this, there are in our world, diminishers and expanders.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.57,1:33:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just showing you all the processes, the chances of knowing what is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.57,1:33:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got four pages of things that can destroy that capacity.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.17,1:33:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,People can generally be divided into minimizers and diministers.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.36,1:33:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Minimizers and expanders.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.84,1:33:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Minimizers say, oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.45,1:33:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And expanders say, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.28,1:33:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, look at that Denmark vendor.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.79,1:33:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And a diminisher will say, oh, that's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.14,1:33:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,$50 worth of paint will fix it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.14,1:33:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.14,1:33:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can diminish or expand.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.50,1:33:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's not within one's conscious control.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.75,1:33:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind just automatically tends to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.75,1:34:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to have a mind that depends on your childhood experiences.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.75,1:34:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether spilling milk was a big deal, or it was a minor deal, don't worry about it, I'll mop it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.75,1:34:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Or whether it was a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.75,1:34:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So diminishing and expanding then comes from childhood training
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.75,1:34:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of what your parents consider to be emotionally important.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.75,1:34:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And they do this by dramatizing it, exaggerating it, or minimizing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.03,1:34:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Also how you interpret things depends on your overall mental capacity.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.03,1:34:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the old Freudian balance of the ego. The Freudian view of the ego is somewhat
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.13,1:34:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,different. It has a more positive view of the ego. It sees that as the mental
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.21,1:34:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,capacity to balance the id, that's one's emotional animal instincts, and the
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.81,1:34:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,superego, which is one's conscience. So in classical Freudian analysis, your ego's
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.56,1:35:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,capacity to get away from excessive guilt, excessive guilt, at the same time
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.48,1:35:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,not give in to your id, which is just an instinctual animal. You can't run around
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.76,1:35:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,raping people. On the other hand, you can't kill yourself because you made a
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.02,1:35:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,slight mistake. So the Freudian ego is defined as reality testing, the capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.45,1:35:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,for reality testing. Balancing the id, which is a crazy animal and is out to
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.33,1:35:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,kill you and everybody else, or the superego, which is punitive. And I think
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.73,1:35:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as I've said, I'm not going to go into too much detail about that, but I think
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.07,1:35:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,as I've said, I'm not going to go into too much detail about that, but I think
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.09,1:35:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told you, when I was young, I had to go for counseling, for, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.31,1:35:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,scrupulosity. The slightest infraction of truth in my viewpoint was like
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.89,1:35:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,unforgivable blot on your soul, and God could see this black spot. So you lived
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.86,1:36:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in dread of having even a passing sinful thought. All right, so generally then, the
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.69,1:36:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,capacity for reality testing, the superego, which is an instinctual animal,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.35,1:36:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,capacity for understanding reality is a balance of mental, emotional health, where
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.09,1:36:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you have balance, you have maturity, and unconscious psychological factors, such
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.91,1:36:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,as poor self-esteem and things like this. Yep. Whether the absolute reality is
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.99,1:36:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,allness or nothingness is a differentiation which we've made in more
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.42,1:36:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced lectures. And then we come to the last one, which I don't understand at
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.86,1:36:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,all, and therefore I'll explain it to you. And that is, what is the absolute reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.52,1:36:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is, what is the absolute reality? And that is, what is the absolute reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.54,1:36:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is, what is the absolute reality? And that is, what is the absolute reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.88,1:36:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is, what is the absolute reality? And that is, what is the absolute reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.38,1:36:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The so-called quantum Zeno effect. Yeah, x-what is the absolute reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.44,1:36:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the more often an
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.25,1:36:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,An absolute reality Ori Magajan
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.37,1:36:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,equation is chosen, the more likely the
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.29,1:36:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.53,1:36:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so-called quantum Zeno
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.77,1:36:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The so-called quantum Zeno
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.19,1:36:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,x- vertex
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.53,1:36:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.57,1:36:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,enser으룪
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.21,1:36:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,option
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.51,1:36:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,no effect. The more often an option is chosen, the more likely the option will
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.35,1:36:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,be chosen again.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.45,1:36:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this has to do with intention and commitment then.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.54,1:37:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The more often you choose to forgive, the more likely you will be to forgive.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.62,1:37:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get this extract
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.16,1:37:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though statistically the options are mathematically the same, length of time
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.58,1:37:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the same, the likelihood is that consciousness, because of its own nature, because you choose
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.58,1:37:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain option, you are more likely to choose that option again.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.52,1:37:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So the more often you choose a benign option, a benign way, you say, well, I could be seeing
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.68,1:37:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,this such and such.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.46,1:37:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you get into a negative thought or a negative fix, you ask yourself, well, how
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.22,1:37:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,could I be seeing this?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.12,1:37:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, that's part of the Course in Miracles, and one reason it works.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.26,1:37:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask the Holy Spirit to recontextualize it so you see it differently, so you see it
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.94,1:37:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,through the eyes of forgiveness, and you see that whatever you're upset about is because
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.69,1:37:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you've stopped time at some particular point, and when you expand it beyond that particular
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.41,1:38:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,point and you see it's sort of an evolutionary revelation, you see the innocence of what
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.37,1:38:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you were just upset about.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.39,1:38:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're really asking God to do is to recontextualize.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.71,1:38:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you're experiencing and comprehending a situation, and that takes you out of right
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.24,1:38:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and wrong and condemnation of yourself and others, and that takes you out of guilt and
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.40,1:38:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,anger and hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.30,1:38:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So the recontextualization then is done as an option because that's your commitment to
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.20,1:38:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,be that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.87,1:38:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now another person doesn't, you know, another person who is not spiritually oriented just
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.65,1:38:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,sees something and hates it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.28,1:38:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels justified, and that's okay with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.66,1:38:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you grow spiritually, the negatives are no longer so pleasantly tolerated.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.10,1:38:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you find they're not welcome anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.24,1:38:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you're used to beautiful music, and some awful music comes on, and you're
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.62,1:38:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,used to beauty now.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.32,1:39:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The worst music in the world is on the Weather Channel.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.70,1:39:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to do something to help God and humanity, write the Weather Channel.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.56,1:39:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They have the worst God-awful.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.40,1:39:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Disharmonic, harmonious music I've ever heard.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.73,1:39:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say this to them, turn it down, I can't stand the music.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.30,1:39:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They have the unhearing ear for bad, bad music.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.08,1:39:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we'll forgive them because after all, the only reason we're looking at it is to
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.74,1:39:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,find out if it's going to rain on the day of the lecture anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.29,1:39:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And our intention must be okay because so far we've had good weather.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.31,1:39:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've given altogether about 50 all-day lectures locally since 2002.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.34,1:39:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We've given another 40 of them or so elsewhere in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.99,1:40:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll be approaching, we'll have given maybe before long 100 all-day lectures, including
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.73,1:40:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,descriptions, slides, lectures, explanations, and sharing oneself to the best of one's ability.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.27,1:40:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is one's, that comes out of one's declaration of one's intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.80,1:40:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is the same intention I had as a physician because I practiced medicine for 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.54,1:40:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was to be helpful in every way that you could to the people entrusted to your care
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.70,1:40:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because you know you're answerable to God for what you did with this person.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.62,1:40:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that you're answerable to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.38,1:40:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And so to be answerable to God for one's life then almost guarantees spiritual purification.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.18,1:40:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.72,1:40:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.84,1:40:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.86,1:40:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.88,1:40:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that you're dedicated to God and that you're answerable to God, then you become
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.61,1:40:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,very aligned with truth and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.18,1:41:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The people that are dangerous in this world are ones who do not believe they're answerable
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.80,1:41:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.80,1:41:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They're dangerous, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.08,1:41:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can trust people who realize, accept, I'm answerable to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.10,1:41:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is a constant state during these lectures, and I realize I'm answerable to God for any
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.42,1:41:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,error I make.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.42,1:41:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared to death of making an error.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.00,1:41:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So you take responsibility for the truth of what you teach others, and people who won't
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.20,1:41:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,take responsibility for the truth of their own teaching are very dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.66,1:41:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But to be responsible.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.60,1:41:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So I accept responsibility for the truth of all I have conveyed, and I accept responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.36,1:41:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,if I have made any errors, because I've done them unwittingly.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.02,1:42:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So I feel the teacher should recommit his devotion to the truth and to his students
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.58,1:42:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and restate what his commitment is, what the commitment of his life is.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.89,1:42:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So as each one of us does that by declaration, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.54,1:42:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We become responsible.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.86,1:42:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We become that, which counterbalances the negativity of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.86,1:42:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because how many people are willing to do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.38,1:42:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Only a group like this is willing to really stake your answerability to God for the integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.86,1:42:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,by which you do your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.24,1:42:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean you can't make a mistake, but it was an honest mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.97,1:42:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if it was not an honest mistake, you then admit that it was not an honest mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.53,1:42:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I contrive that.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.81,1:42:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to feel sorry for myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.37,1:42:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I make everybody else look bad, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.19,1:42:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So even then, the truth gets you out of a falsehood, out of an error, by telling the
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.03,1:42:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,truth about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.03,1:42:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, well, my ego just wanted to be right about it, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.41,1:42:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And I mean, the Weather Channel does that bad music.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.57,1:43:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, I remember the director of music there, I don't know, would never have passed
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.95,1:43:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the seashore music ability test with, I don't know, I never would have made it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.34,1:43:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.34,1:43:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.34,1:43:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see our last slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.34,1:43:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to shut them up otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.34,1:43:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.34,1:43:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,God, this comes from my wonderful editor.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.27,1:43:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,She found this somewhere out there in blogger land or internet land, WW internet world.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.76,1:43:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think it's so wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.28,1:44:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So I may not have gotten it across verbally, one of the questions in the last lecture,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.04,1:44:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,she said, I said, oh my God, I have missed completely.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.04,1:44:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Making the difference between appearance and essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.43,1:44:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What percentage of politicians, let's ask something about politicians.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.40,1:44:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The majority of the politicians lie routinely.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.02,1:44:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's part of their job.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.49,1:44:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, please don't quote a politician as the source of authority.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.96,1:44:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The politician is supposed to make things work by whatever means, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.66,1:44:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,His commitment is not a spiritual one.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.66,1:44:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no point in making a politician wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.26,1:44:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He has to make the thing work by whatever means he can to make it work, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.73,1:44:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And if he tells everybody, if they do it this way, this is going to happen, everybody's
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.39,1:44:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.91,1:45:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And as far as he sees, he's fulfilling the good and the good is the fulfillment of a
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.47,1:45:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,certain specified objective.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.35,1:45:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So a spiritual person has a different whole set of what is integrous, what is truth, what
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.83,1:45:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is honesty and what is reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.11,1:45:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But isn't that adorable?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.11,1:45:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.79,1:45:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I just get such a kick out of that, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.75,1:45:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason I emphasize this so much is because I was surprised when we calibrated
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.66,1:45:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Wolf and Sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.95,1:45:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I was surprised.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.95,1:45:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It only came out at 120.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:28.95,1:45:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, wow, that's worse than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.00,1:45:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Because a lot of political bullshit is, calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.82,1:45:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, well, it's going to be 190 coming out of prideful egotism, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.72,1:45:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it came out at 120.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.77,1:45:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Which 120 then means.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.73,1:45:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That it is the hiding place of evil itself, that what you're looking at is evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.30,1:45:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why 120.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.04,1:45:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why it's so important to become sophisticated and realize essence is one thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.04,1:46:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,perception is another.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.13,1:46:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This calibrates at 120.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.87,1:46:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I just think that's very, very significant.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.78,1:46:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a serious error, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.84,1:46:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just a minor one to be, to misperceive.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:12.24,1:46:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,To take advantage of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.24,1:46:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a serious error.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.24,1:46:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just a minor one.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.47,1:46:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that the Komodo dragon is safe because you're a humanitarian, you love all of nature,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.71,1:46:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,blah, blah, blah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.71,1:46:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't mean you can step in the cage with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.10,1:46:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So the downside of Western civilization is it's lost that capacity.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.34,1:46:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to be nice to all the Komodo dragons and invite them here.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.87,1:46:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're just nice animals.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.59,1:46:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Just nice animals.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:41.59,1:46:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So that error is quite severe at 120.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:43.99,1:46:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I thought this.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:45.99,1:46:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This teaches in one glance, you know, what it would take a number of lectures to get
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.41,1:46:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,across to many people.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:53.78,1:47:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself have been deceived by the sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.22,1:47:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody else here ever been deceived by the sheep's clothing?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.61,1:47:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.33,1:47:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think, I thought one picture is worth a thousand words.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.07,1:47:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why we brought it to people's awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:18.99,1:47:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.99,1:47:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, now let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:25.56,1:47:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are we on time?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:26.56,1:47:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I get you to watch.
